<d>
  <d name="en">
    <xhtml name="short">Denoising using overcomplete Local PCA </xhtml>
    <d name="parameters">
      <xhtml name="patch_radius">size in voxel of the local patch to be taken around each voxel. Default size is 2 </xhtml>
      <xhtml name="brain_mask">Mask of the brain to avoid estimating the noise outside the brain. </xhtml>
      <xhtml name="denoised_dwi_data"/>
      <xhtml name="tau_factor">thresholding factor for pca eigenvalues:  \tau = (\tau_{factor} \sigma)^2
</xhtml>
      <xhtml name="sigma">Standard deviation of the noise estimated using PIESNO algorithm</xhtml>
      <xhtml name="method">Computation method used to perform Principal Component Analysis. Possible values are:
eigen values decomposition (eig)
singular values decomposition (svd)
</xhtml>
      <xhtml name="dwi_data">Diffusion data volume (4D volume) </xhtml>
    </d>
    <xhtml name="long">Diffusion data denoising using overcomplete local principal component analysis. We rely on the Dipy implementation based on:
Reference: J. V. Manjon, P. Coup√©, L. Concha, A. Buades, D. L. Collins, M. Robles. Diffusion Weighted Image Denoising using overcomplete Local PCA. PLoS ONE 8(9): e73021. doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0073021</xhtml>
  </d>
</d>
